Defendant John W Gemeinhardt in court with attorney Basil Martin Loeb.  David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count #2 is dismissed and read in.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

30 DAYS JAIL;

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION: To be left to the discretion of the probation agent;

COURT COSTS:  $243.00  (to be paid as a condition of probation);

COMMUNITY SERVICE: 50 HOURS (to be performed as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
  Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,   immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.

The Court will grants early termination of probation after 9 months if recommended by the agent;
